<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 341.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi><hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 15, 1862.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Just at the moment when the mail is about
                            to close authentic information reaches the government that the insurgent
                            forces which have been approaching and menacing Cincinnati and
                            Louisville have receded, and are retreating in Kentucky. The alarm in
                            that quarter has passed.</p>
                        <p>The press has already announced that the insurgent army, which has been
                            threatening Washington, Baltimore, and Pennsylvania, evacuated Frederick
                            on the 12th instant. I now give you a despatch which has just been
                            received from Major General McClellan, which shows the position of the
                            two armies at the present moment.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>